# Awesome Project

A small example project to demonstrate a clean GitHub repository structure, CI, and tests.

## Features
- Simple Python command-line tool
- Unit tests with `pytest`
- CI with GitHub Actions
- MIT License

## Requirements
- Python 3.8+

## Install
```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/awesome-project.git
cd awesome-project
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate   # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python -m src.main "Hello, GitHub!"
pytest

